Estonian Air to Replace CEO Aljas From June, Aeripaeev Reports

-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 
2011-05-09T10:46:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/estonian-air-to-replace-ceo-aljas-from-june-aeripaeev-reports.html
AS Estonian Air, the Baltic country’s
national carrier, will replace Chief Executive Andrus Aljas from
June 1,  Aeripaeev  reported, citing Chairman Joakim Helenius.  The man replacing Aljas as management board head isn’t
Estonian and has long international experience in the airline
business, Helenius was cited as saying in an interview. The new
CEO will need to focus on adding flight connections and making
them profitable, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
 oummelas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  